1
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:46,720
MEDITERRANEAN SEA
60 MILES SOUTH OF MARSEILLES

2
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,640
SAILORS:

3
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:51,960
What a mess.

4
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,640
You've never seen a dead man before?

5
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:04,320
Put a blanket on him. Cover him.

6
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,720
I'm coming.

7
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:07,640
Be careful.

8
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:10,120
One minute. I'll be right there. Cover him.

9
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:44,000
BOURNE: What the hell
are you doing to me?

10
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,400
BOURNE: What are you doing?

11
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:50,560
Goddamn it! Where am I?

12
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:54,120
GIANCARLO: A boat! A fishing boat.
You were in the water.

13
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,440
We pulled you out.

14
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,800
BOURNE: What water?

15
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:59,280
GIANCARLO: You were shot. See?
There are the bullets.

16
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:04,880
GIANCARLO: Look, there is a number
for a bank. Why was it in your hip?

17
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,160
BOURNE: My hip?

18
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,880
- Why was it in your hip?
- My hip.

19
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,640
Yeah, in your hip under the skin.

20
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,000
BOURNE: Oh, God.

21
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:13,880
BOURNE: What are you doing with me?
GIANCARLO: You need to rest.

22
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:15,560
Please. Lie down.

23
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:18,520
I'm a friend. I'm your friend.

24
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,480
My name is Giancarlo.

25
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,400
Who are you?

26
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,160
GIANCARLO: What's your name?

27
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,400
What's your name?

28
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:29,960
BOURNE: I don't know.

29
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:33,880
BOURNE: Oh, God.
GIANCARLO: Lie down.

30
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:40,880
CENTRAL INTELLIGENCE AGENCY
LANGLEY, VIRGINIA

31
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:02,640
It's been confirmed, sir. Mission failed.

32
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,360
BOURNE:

33
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,200
Do you know who I am?

34
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:51,680
I do not know who I am.

35
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,040
BOURNE:

36
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,480
Tell me who I am.

37
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,440
If you know who I am...

38
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,680
Please stop messing around...

39
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:07,720
...and tell me.

40
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,920
GIANCARLO: If you want to eat, get in there.

41
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:24,600
BOURNE: Based on these charts,
I think I may have been closer to the coast.

42
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:27,360
What is this? You tie these knots?

43
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:31,160
GIANCARLO: So, it starts to come back?
BOURNE: No, it doesn't.

44
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:34,080
The knot's like everything else.
I found the rope and I did it.

45
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,720
Same way I can read.

46
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,280
I can write. I can add, subtract.
I can make coffee.

47
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:41,800
BOURNE: I can shuffle cards, play chess.
GIANCARLO: Yes, it will come back.

48
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:45,080
No, it's not coming back, goddamn it!
That's the point!

49
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:47,720
I'm down here looking through this,
all this shit!

50
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,680
For two weeks I'm down here.

51
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:52,840
It's not working.
I don't even know what to look for.

52
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:59,480
You need to rest. It will come back.

53
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:02,080
BOURNE: What if it doesn't come back?

54
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:07,760
We get in there tomorrow,
I don't even have a name.

55
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:40,560
It's not much,
but it should get you to Switzerland.

56
00:08:44,160 --> 00:08:45,480
Thank you.

57
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,520
ZURICH COPS:

58
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,440
Can't you read the signs?

59
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,480
On your feet... let's go... right now.

60
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:28,760
The park is closed.
There's no sleeping in the park.

61
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,320
BOURNE: All right.

62
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,640
Let's see some identification.

63
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,560
BOURNE: No, I don't...

64
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:35,800
Come on... your papers.

65
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,680
I don't have any papers. I lost my...

66
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,720
I've lost them... my papers... they are lost.

67
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,800
Ok... let's go... put your hands up.

68
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,720
...I just need to sleep...

69
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:12,960
These people have threatened my family.
My babies.

70
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:15,320
So I'm telling you,
when the evidence is clear...

71
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:17,880
...I will have a nice story
for you to read about.

72
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:21,040
And all my friends out there,
you will read about yourselves.

73
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:22,760
If you want to play this game...

74
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:26,040
...after I have been reasonable,
I will show you.

75
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:29,960
That's Nykwana Wombosi speaking in Paris
the day before yesterday.

76
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,680
He was an irritation before he took power,
a problem...

77
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:36,240
...when he was in power,
and he's been a disaster for us in exile.

78
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,760
He's writing a book
about the Agency's history in Africa.

79
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,240
He's going to name names.

80
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:43,360
It's basically a shakedown.
He's demanding the Agency's help.

81
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:47,080
He wants us to put him back in power
in six months, or else.

82
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:50,640
This interview, and I'll make the tape
available to whoever wants it...

83
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:54,240
...he goes on to claim that he's just survived
an assassination attempt.

84
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:57,440
He says it's us. He says he's got proof.

85
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:01,160
The Director wants to know
if there's any truth...

86
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,920
...in this accusation.

87
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:06,960
I've already assured him there's nobody
that reckless on my senior staff.

88
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:16,680
ABBOTT: I was recalling a conversation
we had some time ago.

89
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:18,400
Talking about Treadstone.

90
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:22,160
I seem to remember Wombosi's name
might have come up.

91
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,200
I'm not sure what we're talking about.

92
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:26,920
Someone tried to take him out.

93
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:29,840
Tried and failed.

94
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,440
Was this Treadstone?

95
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,640
You're asking me a direct question?

96
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:37,280
Yes.

97
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,960
I thought you were never gonna do that.

98
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:41,320
What happened?

99
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:47,600
Well, we lost the communication
with our man.

100
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:49,680
This was almost two weeks ago.

101
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:51,760
CONKLIN: We've worked around the clock.

102
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:55,000
We've been sleeping down there.
We're doing everything we can.

103
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:59,000
ABBOTT: And you don't let me know this?
CONKLIN: You never wanted to before.

104
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,080
You never made a mistake before.

105
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:12,680
GEMEINSCHAFT BANK
ZURICH SWITZERLAND

106
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:33,160
What can I do for you?

107
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:37,440
Yes, I'm here about a numbered account.

108
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:42,080
If you just enter your account number here,
I'll direct you to an appropriate officer.

109
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:40,160
My name is Jason Bourne.

110
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:47,520
I live in Paris.

111
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:20,200
I'm trying to think...

112
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:22,360
How long's it been since I was here last?

113
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:23,800
I'm not sure.

114
00:17:24,120 --> 00:17:26,160
It must be three weeks.

115
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:41,280
BOURNE: Yes, in Paris.

116
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:44,240
Do you have the number
for a Jason Bourne?

117
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,800
OPERATOR:
Yes. Would you like me to connect you?

118
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:49,240
BOURNE: Yes, please.

119
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:56,920
BOURNE:
This is 46990384.

120
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,840
Leave a message at the beep.

121
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,560
BOURNE: I'm an American.

122
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:03,680
Okay.

123
00:19:04,560 --> 00:19:05,760
GUARD: Hold it.

124
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:07,480
MARINE 1: You've no jurisdiction here.

125
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:09,080
MARINE 1: Hold it there. Okay?

126
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:14,880
MARIE: No.

127
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:17,480
Excuse me. No.
This is not my current address, okay?

128
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:21,240
This was my address until two days ago,
when I started standing in line.

129
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:23,440
Now I lose my apartment, okay?

130
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:26,320
That means no address, no phone,
no money, no time.

131
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:28,680
- And I still have no visa!
- Miss Kreutz, please.

132
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:30,880
CLERK: I must ask you
to keep your voice down.

133
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:34,080
MARIE: Excuse me. But where's the guy
that I talked to last week?

134
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:36,600
Every week it's a new person.
How am I supposed to...

135
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,120
I don't know who you saw last week.

136
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:40,760
MARIE: Let me help you. I'm sure I have it.
Hang on.

137
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:42,880
CLERK:
Could I have your attention for a moment?

138
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:45,000
MARIE: I have it right here. Just look at it.

139
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:49,240
CLERK: You staged an effort to circumvent
the immigration laws of the United States.

140
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,400
MARIE: This is a student visa now.

141
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:54,320
It's not about a green card anymore.
It's very different.

142
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:59,400
CLERK: It's not a menu. You don't just...
MARIE: I brought all this proof.

143
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,920
DISPATCHER: Potential suspect...

144
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,000
Help in assault incident.

145
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:08,360
You! Red bag! The red bag!

146
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:11,240
SECURITY CHIEF:
Stop right there! Put your hands up!

147
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,240
MAN: I'm on it.

148
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:57,800
SECURITY CHIEF: Move it! Now!
Now! Move!

149
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:04,080
Alpha Unit, take the back stairs
and work your way up. Bravo...

150
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:13,400
SECURITY CHIEF: Move in! Move in!

151
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,200
MARINE 1: Okay, clear!

152
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:18,400
SECURITY CHIEF: Suspect is...

153
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:21,400
BRAVO LEADER: Moving up staircase.
Proceeding to second floor.

154
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:27,840
SECURITY CHIEF: Alpha Unit, you're clear.

155
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,840
MARINE 2: Move! Move!

156
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:40,920
SECURITY CHIEF:
All Units, target may have a radio.

157
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,960
Go to Code 77. Over.

158
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:45,080
Code 77, copy.

159
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,600
MARINE 3: The floor! Down!

160
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:49,640
MARINE 4: Clear!

161
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:12,440
MARINE 2: Go. Move up.

162
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:18,680
CONKLIN: He's in Zurich now? Right now?
ZORN: Yes. It just came in.

163
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:22,080
- They're sure it's him?
- Yes. He went to the bank.

164
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:24,040
Our source at the bank, that's who called.

165
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:25,160
CONKLIN: Come on.

166
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:27,720
But he's got to assume
we're watching the bank, right?

167
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,840
CONKLIN: I don't know. Come on.

168
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,920
I mean, he cleaned out the box.
He left a gun. What does that mean?

169
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,600
I said I don't know!

170
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:36,960
I liked it better when I thought he was dead.

171
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:54,720
What are you looking at?

172
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:56,320
I heard you inside.

173
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:57,240
MARIE: What?

174
00:24:57,320 --> 00:25:01,040
The consulate. I heard you talking.
I thought maybe we could help each other.

175
00:25:01,120 --> 00:25:02,160
How's that?

176
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,680
BOURNE:
You need money. I need a ride out of here.

177
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:07,680
I'm not running a car service. Thank you.

178
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:10,760
I'll give you $10,000 to drive me to Paris.

179
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:13,640
What, do you think I'm a fool?

180
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:15,720
You'd be a fool not to take it.

181
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:22,200
MARIE: Is this a joke? Some kind of scam?
BOURNE: No, it's no scam.

182
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:25,240
BOURNE: I'll give you another $10,000
when we arrive.

183
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:26,960
MARIE: Jesus.

184
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:36,520
- Is that for you?
- Look. You drive, I pay. It's that simple.

185
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,920
I got enough trouble, okay?

186
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:44,200
BOURNE: Okay.

187
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,200
Can I have my money back?

188
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:03,160
CONKLIN: All right, go. Keep going.

189
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:04,800
CONKLIN: Go.

190
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,760
- There! Wait!
- No, it's got to be near the end.

191
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:10,720
Come on, folks! We caught a break here!
Let's go!

192
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:11,880
COMM TECH 1: Okay, I'm up.

193
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,880
COMM TECH 1: We're getting grids.
Airline, train, hotels, hospitals.

194
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:17,360
- Who's getting the address? The street?
- Gemensheidt.

195
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:19,520
RESEARCH TECH 1: Here we go.
I think I got it.

196
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:20,880
ZORN: Is it him?

197
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:22,520
RESEARCH TECH 2: Unreal.

198
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:24,480
RESEARCH TECH 1: This is 38 minutes ago.

199
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:27,960
ZORN: Zurich police are looking
for an American carrying a red bank bag.

200
00:26:28,040 --> 00:26:31,720
ZORN: He just tore up the embassy and
put two cops in the hospital last night.

201
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:36,840
Get everybody up. Do it now.
I want them all activated.

202
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:38,680
Wait. All of them? At the same time?

203
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:42,240
You heard me.
I want Bourne in a body bag by sundown.

204
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:46,040
CONKLIN: All right, let's get a map up here!
Come on, folks! Let's work it!

205
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,160
COMM TECH 1:
The grids are getting updated.

206
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:08,000
MARIE: Which was fine with me
because I was ready.

207
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:10,960
After six months in Amsterdam,
you're not sure...

208
00:28:11,040 --> 00:28:13,560
...if you've been there 20 minutes or years,
you know.

209
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:16,680
So I went. I took all the money I had.
I went in with friends...

210
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:20,960
...we took over this really cool surf shop
outside Biarritz, right by the water.

211
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:22,520
It was amazing.

212
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:27,240
It was just amazing for about three months,
until it turned out that this...

213
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:31,680
...jerk who had fronted us the lease
was actually shining everyone on and...

214
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:39,320
And what?

215
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:42,920
What do you mean "what"? Listen to me.

216
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:45,480
I've been speed-talking
for about 60 kilometres now.

217
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:48,680
I talk when I'm nervous.
I mean, I talk like this when I'm nervous.

218
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:51,080
- I'm gonna shut up now.
- No, don't do that.

219
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:55,040
I haven't talked to anybody in a while.

220
00:28:55,680 --> 00:28:58,240
Yeah, but we're not talking. I'm talking.

221
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:01,440
You've said,
like, 10 words since we left Zurich.

222
00:29:01,520 --> 00:29:04,080
Well, listening to you, it's relaxing.

223
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:08,840
I haven't slept in a while and...

224
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:11,360
And I've had this headache.

225
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:13,760
It's like a constant thing in my head...

226
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:17,000
...and it's just starting
to move to the background...

227
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:18,520
...so keep going.

228
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:22,000
Really, if you want, please keep talking.

229
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:25,840
Okay.

230
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:29,480
What kind of music do you like?

231
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:34,320
What do you like? Come on.

232
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:37,880
- You know what? Never mind.
- No, it's fine. Tell me.

233
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,600
What do you want to listen to?

234
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,680
I don't know.

235
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:45,760
Come on, it's not that hard.
What do you like? Tell me.

236
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:47,240
I don't know.

237
00:29:57,280 --> 00:29:59,880
Who pays $20,000 for a ride to Paris?

238
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:10,760
Fuck it.

239
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:15,040
I can't remember anything
that happened before two weeks ago.

240
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:18,080
- Lucky you.
- No, I'm serious.

241
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:21,960
I don't know who I am.
