01:00:17,960 --> 01:00:19,440
Why? Where are we going?

489
01:00:19,560 --> 01:00:22,320
BOURNE: I need to go to the hotel
where John Michael Kane stayed.

490
01:00:22,400 --> 01:00:23,880
The Hotel Regina.

491
01:00:24,880 --> 01:00:28,200
If I was him,
then they're gonna have some records.

492
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:30,320
We need that hotel bill.

493
01:00:30,400 --> 01:00:31,400
MARIE: Okay.

494
01:00:31,800 --> 01:00:34,320
It gets slightly complicated, though.

495
01:00:35,200 --> 01:00:36,880
Because you're dead.

496
01:00:38,680 --> 01:00:39,840
BOURNE: Right.

497
01:00:44,360 --> 01:00:47,320
BODYGUARD: Please.
WOMBOSl: They want war, we'll make war.

498
01:00:47,400 --> 01:00:50,720
If they want to kill me,
they better kill me the first time.

499
01:00:50,840 --> 01:00:54,120
They better kill me dead.
They better kill me when I'm in my sleep.

500
01:00:54,200 --> 01:00:56,440
BODYGUARD: Listen to me.
We need these people.

501
01:00:56,720 --> 01:00:59,120
It's hard enough getting people
that we know to help us.

502
01:00:59,200 --> 01:01:00,560
BODYGUARD: We must be careful.

503
01:01:00,640 --> 01:01:01,680
We?

504
01:01:02,320 --> 01:01:03,280
No, you.

505
01:01:03,480 --> 01:01:06,080
You need to bring me back
that bastard kid's head...

506
01:01:06,160 --> 01:01:09,560
...put it in front of this house,
and show them the war we're fighting.

507
01:01:09,640 --> 01:01:10,920
But that is precisely...

508
01:01:16,280 --> 01:01:17,600
BODYGUARD: Nykwana!

509
01:01:28,360 --> 01:01:31,560
BOURNE: We'll give the watch
a reference check before we go.

510
01:01:33,360 --> 01:01:34,440
MARIE: Okay.

511
01:01:36,720 --> 01:01:38,800
What's the pay phone number?

512
01:01:39,280 --> 01:01:41,440
MARIE: 616-2468.

513
01:01:41,560 --> 01:01:42,680
Exits?

514
01:01:42,840 --> 01:01:44,040
There's three.

515
01:01:44,240 --> 01:01:48,240
Service at the back,
side goes to the street past the shops...

516
01:01:48,600 --> 01:01:50,200
...front is the best.

517
01:01:50,440 --> 01:01:54,160
If I think I'm being followed, I walk out
with the bag over my right shoulder.

518
01:01:54,240 --> 01:01:55,680
And if there's no taxi?

519
01:01:55,760 --> 01:01:59,280
I keep on walking,
don't look back until you make contact.

520
01:02:02,320 --> 01:02:03,400
MARIE: What?

521
01:02:07,520 --> 01:02:09,200
We need this, right?

522
01:02:11,960 --> 01:02:13,000
Okay.

523
01:02:23,760 --> 01:02:25,160
BOURNE: I need distances.

524
01:02:25,760 --> 01:02:28,440
You walk in, you pick a spot.
Some midpoint in the lobby.

525
01:02:28,840 --> 01:02:31,880
Count your steps to that spot,
and then remember that number.

526
01:02:31,960 --> 01:02:34,360
Because after I call you,
I can get you moving.

527
01:02:34,440 --> 01:02:35,880
You understand?

528
01:02:36,520 --> 01:02:37,800
I also need a head count.

529
01:02:37,880 --> 01:02:40,720
How many people from when you walk in
until you get to the desk.

530
01:02:40,800 --> 01:02:43,560
How many hotel employees are there?
And obviously security.

531
01:02:43,680 --> 01:02:45,800
And it might not be that easy
to see who they are.

532
01:02:45,960 --> 01:02:49,360
So I'll call you, you give me the layout,
and we'll take it from there.

533
01:02:53,760 --> 01:02:54,800
OPERATOR: Regina.

534
01:02:54,880 --> 01:02:56,880
Yes, the house phone in the lobby.

535
01:03:14,600 --> 01:03:16,160
BOURNE: What happened?
MARIE: L...

536
01:03:16,280 --> 01:03:19,160
BOURNE: Did something go wrong?
MARIE: I've got the records.

537
01:03:20,560 --> 01:03:23,360
He, this guy at the front desk
was smiling at me.

538
01:03:23,440 --> 01:03:27,120
So I thought, you know, all this trouble,
maybe it's easier to just ask for them.

539
01:03:27,200 --> 01:03:30,080
BOURNE: You have the bill?
MARIE: He made me a photocopy.

540
01:03:31,520 --> 01:03:33,320
You just asked for it?

541
01:03:34,560 --> 01:03:37,520
I said I was Mr. Kane's personal assistant.

542
01:03:42,080 --> 01:03:44,280
BOURNE: Okay. That's good thinking.

543
01:03:53,360 --> 01:03:55,240
ZORN: Sir, can l...
ABBOTT: No.

544
01:03:58,640 --> 01:04:02,320
ABBOTT: Wombosi was assassinated
in his house in the middle of Paris.

545
01:04:03,280 --> 01:04:05,000
Yeah, we just heard.

546
01:04:05,520 --> 01:04:08,520
It's him. It's Bourne. We're almost positive.

547
01:04:08,640 --> 01:04:10,840
He had an assignment. He failed.

548
01:04:10,920 --> 01:04:13,840
He obviously felt compelled
to finish the task.

549
01:04:13,920 --> 01:04:14,760
ABBOTT: Jesus.

550
01:04:14,840 --> 01:04:16,800
CONKLIN: We think he'll come back in now.

551
01:04:17,400 --> 01:04:18,800
I mean, it's routine.

552
01:04:18,880 --> 01:04:20,640
It's like behavioural software.

553
01:04:22,320 --> 01:04:24,280
He's following a protocol.

554
01:04:24,640 --> 01:04:28,520
Now that he's completed the mission,
we think he'll come back in.

555
01:04:29,280 --> 01:04:30,760
They always do.

556
01:04:31,600 --> 01:04:32,680
When?

557
01:04:32,960 --> 01:04:34,960
ABBOTT: How long till he checks in?

558
01:04:36,520 --> 01:04:37,760
ZORN: 24 hours.
ABBOTT: 24?

559
01:04:37,840 --> 01:04:39,840
Yeah, it's usually something like that.

560
01:04:41,600 --> 01:04:42,880
ABBOTT: Then what?

561
01:04:43,920 --> 01:04:46,000
I told you we'd clean this up.

562
01:04:46,080 --> 01:04:47,680
It will be clean.

563
01:04:51,960 --> 01:04:55,240
BOURNE: I understand you're a dive shop,
but where are you located?

564
01:04:56,720 --> 01:04:58,040
BOURNE: Marseilles?

565
01:05:21,560 --> 01:05:23,600
BOURNE: What specifically does
your company supply?

566
01:05:23,720 --> 01:05:26,720
DIVE SHOP EMPLOYEE: I am sorry.
What is your name, monsieur?

567
01:05:33,320 --> 01:05:34,400
COP:

568
01:05:34,480 --> 01:05:37,840
You've been here for three hours
and you still can't find a print?

569
01:05:46,200 --> 01:05:48,880
CONKLIN: What?
ZORN: Paris police found the vehicle.

570
01:06:01,400 --> 01:06:05,640
RAWLINS: You've reached Simon Rawlins
at Alliance Security, Maritime Division.

571
01:06:05,720 --> 01:06:09,280
Paris office hours are
from 8.00 a. M. To 5.00 p. M.

572
01:06:09,680 --> 01:06:11,480
BOURNE: I got a lead in Paris.

573
01:06:12,200 --> 01:06:14,760
The rest were Marseilles,
and two out in Southampton.

574
01:06:14,880 --> 01:06:17,160
- Paris? It's what?
- Alliance Security. Simon Rawlins.

575
01:06:17,240 --> 01:06:18,360
I got a machine.

576
01:06:42,560 --> 01:06:43,920
SECRETARY: Mr. Kane?

577
01:06:46,000 --> 01:06:47,360
Mr. Kane!

578
01:06:47,560 --> 01:06:51,160
SECRETARY: How are you?
BOURNE: I'm good. How are you?

579
01:06:55,080 --> 01:06:58,040
Mr. Kane. Come right in.
Please have a seat.

580
01:06:58,120 --> 01:06:59,440
Thank you.

581
01:06:59,840 --> 01:07:02,520
RAWLINS:
So, this is the PalmerJohnson tri-deck.

582
01:07:03,320 --> 01:07:06,960
I'm assuming you're still in the market.
It's still the same vessel?

583
01:07:07,800 --> 01:07:08,800
Yes.

584
01:07:31,800 --> 01:07:32,800
So I'm Kane.

585
01:07:32,920 --> 01:07:34,640
MARIE: They...
BOURNE: I had a meeting as Kane.

586
01:07:34,720 --> 01:07:36,400
- They said...
- No. I'm definitely Kane.

587
01:07:36,480 --> 01:07:39,000
I just had a meeting as Kane
and he knew me as Kane.

588
01:07:39,080 --> 01:07:42,360
So I'm definitely Bourne.
I'm also just definitely Kane.

589
01:07:42,440 --> 01:07:43,440
It's all just boats.

590
01:07:43,520 --> 01:07:45,600
I got blueprints and cameras
and security systems.

591
01:07:45,680 --> 01:07:47,720
I just found John Michael Kane's body.

592
01:07:48,800 --> 01:07:50,360
In a morgue here in Paris.

593
01:07:50,520 --> 01:07:54,960
But if you are John Michael Kane,
whose body do they have?

594
01:08:02,720 --> 01:08:05,280
ATTENDANT: What was the name again?
BOURNE: Kane.

595
01:08:05,440 --> 01:08:06,400
Kane.

596
01:08:06,480 --> 01:08:07,760
BOURNE: John Michael Kane.

597
01:08:07,880 --> 01:08:09,480
John Michael Kane.

598
01:08:14,520 --> 01:08:16,880
Kane. It's number 121.

599
01:08:18,440 --> 01:08:19,600
I want to see the body.

600
01:08:19,680 --> 01:08:22,840
Our boss could come back.
We are not supposed to do that.

601
01:08:23,760 --> 01:08:24,920
Come on.

602
01:08:40,120 --> 01:08:42,360
Is this it? I mean, where is he?

603
01:08:42,600 --> 01:08:44,000
ATTENDANT: I don't know.

604
01:08:45,240 --> 01:08:46,320
What's going on?

605
01:08:46,400 --> 01:08:48,800
This guy has come to see the American.
But the body has disappeared.

606
01:08:48,880 --> 01:08:50,800
They came yesterday evening... his brother.

607
01:08:50,880 --> 01:08:52,280
He's not in the register.

608
01:08:52,520 --> 01:08:54,000
Who are you? What's going on?

609
01:08:54,080 --> 01:08:57,080
- Where's the body that goes in here?
- I said someone came last night.

610
01:08:57,160 --> 01:08:58,720
I know. Where'd they take the body?

611
01:08:58,800 --> 01:09:00,920
Look, this is not a carnival, okay?

612
01:09:01,000 --> 01:09:03,680
People call, they make an appointment,
follow the rules.

613
01:09:03,760 --> 01:09:06,840
Everyone signs in and out.
This is a serious place. Serious work.

614
01:09:06,920 --> 01:09:10,680
- It's not just to come in whenever you like!
- You're right. We didn't sign in.

615
01:09:10,760 --> 01:09:11,880
BOSS: Get the hell out of here.

616
01:09:11,960 --> 01:09:14,640
BOURNE: Fine. I'm just gonna go sign in.
BOSS: Okay, go.

617
01:09:17,800 --> 01:09:19,040
BOURNE: Is this it?

618
01:09:19,200 --> 01:09:21,400
BOSS: You can't take the book.
BOURNE: This is it?

619
01:09:21,480 --> 01:09:23,880
It's okay. There's a pencil in here.
That's fine.

620
01:09:23,960 --> 01:09:26,800
Honey, why don't you go wait outside?
Here it is.

621
01:09:26,880 --> 01:09:28,160
BOSS: We can't have...
BOURNE: Okay.

622
01:09:30,160 --> 01:09:33,520
MARIE: Jason, what just happened in there?
What are you looking for?

623
01:09:33,640 --> 01:09:35,200
BOURNE: Nykwana Wombosi.

624
01:09:35,440 --> 01:09:38,160
Wombosi went to the morgue to visit Kane.

625
01:09:39,200 --> 01:09:40,200
See?

626
01:09:40,720 --> 01:09:43,640
MARIE: So?
BOURNE: He's in the Alliance brochure.

627
01:09:43,720 --> 01:09:44,920
BOURNE: Same guy.

628
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:46,560
This guy knows.

629
01:10:17,760 --> 01:10:21,960
My French sucks. I can't...
It says something about a boat or...

630
01:10:23,640 --> 01:10:27,840
I don't understand. What does it say?
You read it. Tell me. What?

631
01:10:29,720 --> 01:10:33,400
It says that 3 weeks before he was killed,
Mr. Wombosi told police...

632
01:10:33,680 --> 01:10:37,320
...that a man came onto his yacht,
five miles off the coast of Marseilles...

633
01:10:37,560 --> 01:10:39,360
...and tried to kill him.

634
01:10:39,960 --> 01:10:43,440
It says that he chased the man off the boat
and shot him twice in the back.

635
01:10:45,000 --> 01:10:46,440
It says I'm an assassin.

636
01:11:25,880 --> 01:11:27,120
Stop the car.

637
01:11:27,640 --> 01:11:29,840
But no... you said Rue de I...
we're almost there.

638
01:11:29,920 --> 01:11:31,560
Just right here, this is good.

639
01:11:31,720 --> 01:11:32,840
I said stop.

640
01:11:33,400 --> 01:11:34,680
MARIE: What's going on?

641
01:11:35,680 --> 01:11:36,640
Well... what's going on?

642
01:11:36,720 --> 01:11:38,320
MARIE: What the hell are you doing?

643
01:11:38,400 --> 01:11:39,840
BOURNE: Go. Go.
MARIE: What are...

644
01:11:39,920 --> 01:11:41,240
You gave me too much.

645
01:11:41,320 --> 01:11:44,560
BOURNE: We're blown. Come on.
MARIE: Blown? What is "blown"?

646
01:11:44,640 --> 01:11:46,640
Monsieur... your change, your change.

647
01:11:46,720 --> 01:11:49,360
Sir, please... You can't stay here...
You have to leave.

648
01:11:50,720 --> 01:11:52,240
BOURNE: Keep walking.

649
01:11:52,760 --> 01:11:55,560
What do you think they're doing there?
They're on to the hotel.

650
01:11:55,640 --> 01:11:58,360
- No. You don't know that.
- Trust me. Just keep walking.

651
01:12:19,360 --> 01:12:21,840
Are you crazy? What are you doing now?

652
01:12:23,440 --> 01:12:24,560
MARIE: Jason!

653
01:12:25,040 --> 01:12:26,520
BOURNE: This is blown.

654
01:12:34,640 --> 01:12:35,680
BOURNE: Marie?
MARIE: Get away.

655
01:12:35,760 --> 01:12:37,880
BOURNE: Stop right there.
MARIE: Get away from me.

656
01:12:37,960 --> 01:12:39,680
What are you gonna do? Kill me?

657
01:12:39,760 --> 01:12:41,040
BOURNE: Marie.
MARIE: Is that next?

658
01:12:41,120 --> 01:12:43,160
Listen, stay calm. Stay calm.

659
01:12:43,480 --> 01:12:45,560
Whatever we do, we have to do it together.

660
01:12:45,640 --> 01:12:46,920
- We have to be...
- We?

661
01:12:47,000 --> 01:12:50,320
The only thing we had in common
was that neither of us knew who you were.

662
01:12:50,400 --> 01:12:52,240
MARIE: We've passed that now.
BOURNE: Listen!

663
01:12:52,320 --> 01:12:55,600
The police'll find us. The people who took
the picture in the embassy...

664
01:12:55,680 --> 01:12:58,520
...who killed Wombosi,
they're gonna come here and kill us.

665
01:12:58,600 --> 01:13:00,040
The people who you work for.

666
01:13:02,000 --> 01:13:06,040
I will take you wherever you need to go.
I'll take you there. I'll leave you there.

667
01:13:06,120 --> 01:13:08,560
You can do what you want.
You never have to see me again.

668
01:13:08,640 --> 01:13:11,080
BOURNE: But not here.
If we stay here, we die.

669
01:13:18,880 --> 01:13:21,600
Boy, great police work! Really brilliant!

670
01:13:22,040 --> 01:13:25,400
Why don't they just hang out a banner
that says, "Don't come back!"

671
01:13:26,680 --> 01:13:30,280
Jesus Christ!
What is the French word for "stakeout"?

672
01:13:37,480 --> 01:13:39,640
CONKLIN: Okay, this was 16 minutes ago.

673
01:13:40,600 --> 01:13:42,640
This is our starting point.

674
01:13:42,840 --> 01:13:46,240
CONKLIN: Can't fly, trains are risky. Nicky?
NICKY: Here.

675
01:13:46,320 --> 01:13:49,640
I need to know everything
Paris's finest is doing on this.

676
01:13:49,720 --> 01:13:50,840
NICKY: I'm on it.

677
01:13:52,080 --> 01:13:54,600
ABBOTT:
You said 24 hours, and he's not back.

678
01:13:56,160 --> 01:13:58,840
CONKLIN:
No. But we got a good idea where he is.

679
01:13:59,600 --> 01:14:02,240
ABBOTT: You've got a black ops agent
who's off the reservation.

680
01:14:02,320 --> 01:14:05,040
He trashed an American consulate.
He's on the run in Europe.

681
01:14:05,120 --> 01:14:08,040
You don't know why. I got to stand
before an oversight committee.

682
01:14:08,120 --> 01:14:09,760
What will I say about Treadstone?

683
01:14:09,840 --> 01:14:12,000
You're worried about a budget meeting?

684
01:14:12,240 --> 01:14:15,280
We don't take care of this,
we don't make it to the men's room.

685
01:14:16,080 --> 01:14:18,400
Now, is that clear enough for you?

686
01:14:18,520 --> 01:14:20,320
We will burn for this.

687
01:14:21,080 --> 01:14:23,000
We will both of us burn.

688
01:14:24,520 --> 01:14:28,080
CONKLIN: All right, I want two teams.
Daryl, Ray, stay on the grids.

689
01:14:28,440 --> 01:14:30,360
Brian, Harris, Steve...

690
01:14:30,640 --> 01:14:32,320
...I want to work on this girl.

691
01:14:32,480 --> 01:14:35,440
CONKLIN: And this residency pattern?
COMM TECH 1: We started it.

692
01:14:35,520 --> 01:14:36,360
Get it out.

693
01:14:40,720 --> 01:14:43,520
COMM TECH 1: We cross-referenced
numbers from her relatives.

694
01:14:43,600 --> 01:14:45,680
When we found convergence,
we took the numbers...

695
01:14:45,760 --> 01:14:49,760
...back-checked them, ran a search merge
with other data we had, which wasn't much.

696
01:14:49,840 --> 01:14:51,160
Pins. These pins.

697
01:14:51,360 --> 01:14:54,520
These are all the places we think she's lived
in the last six years.

698
01:14:55,040 --> 01:14:57,680
CONKLIN: One, two, three, four, five.

699
01:14:57,880 --> 01:14:59,440
That's our pool.

700
01:15:04,840 --> 01:15:06,160
MARIE: No answer.

701
01:15:06,640 --> 01:15:08,560
How many times you let it ring?

702
01:15:08,960 --> 01:15:12,240
- Look, if you don't want to go, I'll hitch.
- I said I'd take you.

703
01:15:14,280 --> 01:15:16,080
CONKLIN: Those are the targets.

704
01:15:16,480 --> 01:15:20,960
Beg, borrow, hack, tap, bypass!
I don't care what you do!

705
01:15:21,640 --> 01:15:25,760
I want to know everything you can tell me
about what's going on at those locations.

706
01:15:43,240 --> 01:15:45,200
BOURNE: How do you know
he still owns this?

707
01:15:46,680 --> 01:15:49,720
MARIE: Eamon always had money.
He would never sell this.

708
01:16:18,480 --> 01:16:19,600
Marie?

709
01:16:19,680 --> 01:16:20,760
MARIE: What?

710
01:16:22,600 --> 01:16:24,000
We got to go.

711
01:16:24,680 --> 01:16:25,720
What?

712
01:16:26,000 --> 01:16:27,400
We got to go.

713
01:16:30,160 --> 01:16:32,240
I thought it would...

714
01:16:37,160 --> 01:16:40,440
MARIE: Shit, that's Eamon. I'll talk to him.
BOURNE: We're leaving.

715
01:16:43,760 --> 01:16:46,400
Eamon. Surprise.

716
01:16:46,480 --> 01:16:49,640
It's me, Marie. Wow, God...

717
01:16:50,400 --> 01:16:52,480
...there's a really good reason for this.

718
01:16:52,680 --> 01:16:54,200
EAMON: There bloody well better be.

719
01:16:54,280 --> 01:16:56,800
CLAUDIA: Daddy!
EAMON: Hang on. Hang on.

720
01:16:59,200 --> 01:17:01,440
I had no idea you would be here.

721
01:17:01,760 --> 01:17:04,600
Well, why would I be here?
It's only my bloody house, right?

722
01:17:05,440 --> 01:17:06,440
MARIE: Yeah.

723
01:17:07,720 --> 01:17:09,320
Did she get you into this?

724
01:17:11,080 --> 01:17:12,640
It was just gonna be for a day.

725
01:17:12,720 --> 01:17:15,200
Daddy, Alain has to go pee!

726
01:17:16,120 --> 01:17:18,920
All right, all right, come on. Here.
Get out of the car.

727
01:17:20,280 --> 01:17:21,840
Okay, in you go.

728
01:17:22,040 --> 01:17:23,560
EAMON: Come on, Alain.

729
01:17:24,960 --> 01:17:26,000
MARIE: I'm sorry. I...

730
01:17:26,080 --> 01:17:28,720
I thought it would be okay.
But I guess I was wrong.

731
01:17:28,800 --> 01:17:30,280
- Let's find Mummy.
- Mummy?

732
01:17:30,680 --> 01:17:32,640
Mummy is away for two days, thank God.

733
01:17:37,480 --> 01:17:39,400
BOURNE:
You've got yourself all tied up here.

734
01:17:39,840 --> 01:17:40,880
BOURNE: Okay.

735
01:17:44,840 --> 01:17:46,280
What's he do for a living?

736
01:17:47,440 --> 01:17:48,960
He used to be in shipping.

737
01:17:51,800 --> 01:17:53,360
Is he good for you?

738
01:17:53,640 --> 01:17:55,080
Are you happy?

739
01:17:55,440 --> 01:17:57,560
You know me. I try too hard.

740
01:18:20,400 --> 01:18:21,760
Here you go.

741
01:18:22,600 --> 01:18:23,920
Sleep well.

742
01:18:24,000 --> 01:18:25,320
Good night.

743
01:18:26,960 --> 01:18:28,840
BOURNE: I'll sleep on the floor.

744
01:18:34,720 --> 01:18:37,080
CONKLIN: This was when?
RESEARCH TECH 2: 11:45 a. M.

745
01:18:37,280 --> 01:18:39,840
Which is definitely within
the driving range of Paris.

746
01:18:41,280 --> 01:18:43,280
RESEARCH TECH 1:
The call came from a rest stop.

747
01:18:43,360 --> 01:18:45,120
CONKLIN: Yeah. What's this yellow pin?

748
01:18:45,200 --> 01:18:46,960
She spent two months there in 1997.

749
01:18:47,040 --> 01:18:48,800
Closest town is Riom.

750
01:18:51,000 --> 01:18:54,240
We took her family's phone records
and collated the international calls.

751
01:18:54,320 --> 01:18:56,080
They were in Paris at 2.00 a. M.

752
01:18:56,240 --> 01:18:59,000
They can't fly. The train's too dangerous.

753
01:18:59,080 --> 01:19:01,720
He knows better than to go anywhere
we might track him.

754
01:19:02,240 --> 01:19:03,720
So this is our best guess.

755
01:20:00,560 --> 01:20:03,600
- What are you doing?
- The kids. I was worried. I couldn't sleep.

756
01:20:03,680 --> 01:20:05,640
MARIE: You'll wake them up. We got to go.

757
01:20:05,720 --> 01:20:07,600
BOURNE:
I don't want to know who I am anymore.

758
01:20:07,680 --> 01:20:10,680
I don't care. I don't want to know.

759
01:20:13,040 --> 01:20:16,840
MARIE: Come on. We'll talk about...
BOURNE: I want to forget everything.

760
01:20:17,360 --> 01:20:18,400
It's okay.

761
01:20:18,480 --> 01:20:20,640
BOURNE: I don't care who I am
or what I did.

762
01:20:22,160 --> 01:20:23,200
It's okay.

763
01:20:23,280 --> 01:20:24,600
BOURNE: We have this money.

764
01:20:25,960 --> 01:20:27,280
We can hide.

765
01:20:29,800 --> 01:20:32,480
Can we do that?
Is there any chance you can do that?

766
01:20:40,360 --> 01:20:41,720
MARIE: I don't know.

767
01:20:46,920 --> 01:20:48,200
MARIE: Come on.

768
01:20:55,320 --> 01:20:57,520
CLAUDIA: Here, boy! Here, boy!

769
01:21:00,360 --> 01:21:01,520
'Morning.

770
01:21:02,000 --> 01:21:04,040
EAMON: Christ. You were up early.

771
01:21:04,600 --> 01:21:06,240
Bless you for making coffee.

772
01:21:14,840 --> 01:21:16,520
One night. You weren't kidding.

773
01:21:17,200 --> 01:21:18,600
For a change.

774
01:21:19,080 --> 01:21:20,880
He's not there either.

775
01:21:21,760 --> 01:21:24,440
EAMON: And you looked by the car?
CLAUDIA: He's not anywhere.

776
01:21:25,400 --> 01:21:27,080
All right, let me get dressed.

777
01:21:27,160 --> 01:21:29,560
BOURNE: Who?
EAMON: Bloody dog's gone missing.

778
01:21:29,720 --> 01:21:31,240
Does that happen a lot?

779
01:21:31,320 --> 01:21:33,680
What? That mutt?
Miss his breakfast? Not a chance.

780
01:21:33,760 --> 01:21:35,520
It's always something, right?

781
01:21:37,800 --> 01:21:39,480
Get in the basement.

782
01:21:39,760 --> 01:21:40,840
What?

783
01:21:41,760 --> 01:21:44,600
- Get everyone in the basement.
- What are you talking about?

784
01:21:44,680 --> 01:21:47,960
You're in danger. Your family's in danger.
I don't have time to explain.

785
01:21:48,040 --> 01:21:49,880
EAMON: Wait a minute. What...
MARIE: Eamon.

786
01:21:50,000 --> 01:21:51,320
You should go.

787
01:21:51,400 --> 01:21:53,920
EAMON: What have you done?
BOURNE: It's not her. It's me.

788
01:21:54,000 --> 01:21:57,320
You need to get out of sight
and in the basement as quick as you can.

789
01:21:57,880 --> 01:21:59,040
CLAUDIA: Daddy.

790
01:22:03,920 --> 01:22:05,200
I'm sorry.

791
01:22:05,600 --> 01:22:06,840
Let's go.

792
01:22:24,560 --> 01:22:26,440
MARIE: The phone is dead.
BOURNE: Yeah.

793
01:22:27,680 --> 01:22:30,080
Jason, who's out there? Who is it?

794
01:22:46,840 --> 01:22:48,240
MARIE: What are you doing?

795
01:22:49,000 --> 01:22:50,200
Oh, no.

796
01:22:54,280 --> 01:22:57,240
We should never have come here.
I... These children...

797
01:22:57,320 --> 01:22:58,680
That's not gonna happen.

798
01:25:20,520 --> 01:25:23,240
BOURNE: Where is it? Where's the weapon?

799
01:25:26,720 --> 01:25:29,680
Who else is out here?
Who else? How many you got with you?

800
01:25:29,760 --> 01:25:31,320
BOURNE: I'm not gonna ask you again.

801
01:25:32,160 --> 01:25:34,040
I work alone. Like you.

802
01:25:36,640 --> 01:25:38,360
We always work alone.

803
01:25:38,720 --> 01:25:41,240
BOURNE: What do you mean?
PROFESSOR: Who are you? Rome?

804
01:25:41,320 --> 01:25:42,400
Paris?

805
01:25:44,480 --> 01:25:46,120
Treadstone, both of us.

806
01:25:46,200 --> 01:25:47,800
BOURNE: Treadstone?
PROFESSOR: Which one?

807
01:25:47,880 --> 01:25:49,400
Paris. I live in Paris.

808
01:25:49,480 --> 01:25:51,080
PROFESSOR: You get the headaches?

809
01:25:52,000 --> 01:25:52,960
Yeah.

810
01:25:53,040 --> 01:25:54,960
I get such bad headaches.

811
01:25:55,480 --> 01:25:57,760
You know at night
when you're driving a car?

812
01:25:57,840 --> 01:25:59,440
Maybe it's the headlights.

813
01:25:59,520 --> 01:26:01,200
What is Treadstone?

814
01:26:02,080 --> 01:26:04,120
Treadstone said pills.

815
01:26:05,880 --> 01:26:07,680
They said go to Paris.

816
01:26:07,920 --> 01:26:10,040
Is Treadstone in Paris?

817
01:26:12,200 --> 01:26:13,640
Look at this.

818
01:26:15,720 --> 01:26:17,600
Look at what they make you give.

819
01:26:41,520 --> 01:26:43,280
EAMON: All right, all right.

820
01:26:43,440 --> 01:26:46,200
All right, Claudia,
get in the front and put your belt on.

821
01:26:46,280 --> 01:26:48,440
EAMON:
All right, we're gonna put you in the back.

822
01:26:48,520 --> 01:26:50,560
All right, get in the front, Claudia.

823
01:26:55,520 --> 01:26:57,480
EAMON: I'm not waiting, Marie.

824
01:26:57,720 --> 01:26:59,480
- One minute, Eamon.
- I'm not waiting!

825
01:26:59,560 --> 01:27:01,120
MARIE: Please!

826
01:27:02,160 --> 01:27:03,280
Take it.

827
01:27:03,360 --> 01:27:05,680
BOURNE: I took out $30,000.
The rest is yours.

828
01:27:06,640 --> 01:27:08,520
MARIE: That's it?
BOURNE: That's all I got.

829
01:27:11,320 --> 01:27:12,760
No, that's not what I meant.

830
01:27:12,840 --> 01:27:17,200
This is not gonna stop, Marie.
You got to get out now. Away from me.

831
01:27:18,600 --> 01:27:21,000
BOURNE: You got to get out.
You got to start running.

832
01:27:21,520 --> 01:27:23,160
You get low, you stay low.

833
01:27:23,240 --> 01:27:25,040
No more friends. Nothing familiar.

834
01:27:27,280 --> 01:27:30,840
There's enough in there for you
to make a life. Any life.

835
01:27:30,920 --> 01:27:32,240
EAMON: I'm out of here, Marie!

836
01:27:32,320 --> 01:27:33,360
BOURNE: Hey!

837
01:27:36,000 --> 01:27:38,280
Get in the car. You got to go.

838
01:27:43,640 --> 01:27:45,440
What are you gonna do?

839
01:27:46,240 --> 01:27:47,440
I'll end it.

840
01:27:48,160 --> 01:27:49,400
Go ahead.

841
01:27:51,000 --> 01:27:52,160
BOURNE: Please.

842
01:29:07,400 --> 01:29:08,920
Code in, please.

843
01:29:09,880 --> 01:29:11,080
ZORN: Code in.

844
01:29:15,200 --> 01:29:16,400
Code in.

845
01:29:20,520 --> 01:29:21,880
BOURNE: Who is this?

846
01:29:27,440 --> 01:29:29,160
Who the hell are you?

847
01:29:32,680 --> 01:29:34,360
The man you sent is dead.

848
01:29:34,440 --> 01:29:36,720
So whoever this is, you better start talking.

849
01:29:38,400 --> 01:29:39,520
CONKLIN: Hello, Jason.

850
01:29:40,840 --> 01:29:42,720
So, what are we into now?

851
01:29:47,880 --> 01:29:51,200
It only goes two ways. Either you come in
and let us make this right...

852
01:29:51,320 --> 01:29:53,280
...or we'll keep going until we're satisfied.

853
01:29:53,360 --> 01:29:55,080
You mean until you kill me.

854
01:29:56,960 --> 01:29:59,440
I can't fix this
if I don't know what the problem is.

855
01:29:59,520 --> 01:30:02,040
Tell me what we're into,
and I'll do the best I can.

856
01:30:09,960 --> 01:30:12,400
Why don't you talk to Marie, Jason?

857
01:30:14,160 --> 01:30:17,920
CONKLIN: Let's ask Marie what she wants.
BOURNE: I don't think she gives a shit.

858
01:30:18,000 --> 01:30:19,320
She's dead.

859
01:30:27,920 --> 01:30:30,320
I'm sorry to hear that.
How did that happen?

860
01:30:30,440 --> 01:30:32,280
BOURNE: She was slowing me down.

861
01:30:33,440 --> 01:30:36,080
CONKLIN: All we've been doing right from...
BOURNE: Enough.

862
01:30:36,160 --> 01:30:37,120
Enough.

863
01:30:38,400 --> 01:30:40,640
5:30 p. M. Paris.

864
01:30:40,840 --> 01:30:42,480
Today. Pont Neuf.

865
01:30:42,760 --> 01:30:45,080
Come alone,
you walk to the middle of that bridge.

866
01:30:45,200 --> 01:30:47,320
You take off your jacket. Face east.

867
01:30:47,400 --> 01:30:49,240
BOURNE: I'll redial this number.
CONKLIN: Wait!

868
01:30:58,920 --> 01:31:03,160
First flight out. Tell Nicky I'll call
from the car. Tell her to find Picot. Go.

869
01:31:06,000 --> 01:31:07,160
ABBOTT: So...

870
01:31:07,840 --> 01:31:09,280
What are we gonna do?

871
01:31:09,480 --> 01:31:11,680
I told you I'd clean this up.
That's what I'm doing.

872
01:31:11,760 --> 01:31:13,360
Can you really bring him in?

873
01:31:14,280 --> 01:31:16,040
I think we're past that, don't you?

874
01:31:16,640 --> 01:31:18,200
Do you have a better idea?

875
01:31:18,280 --> 01:31:20,880
You've given me nothing
but a trail of collateral damage...

876
01:31:20,960 --> 01:31:23,240
...from Zurich to Paris.
I couldn't do much worse.

877
01:31:23,320 --> 01:31:26,040
Why don't you go upstairs
and book a conference room?

878
01:31:26,120 --> 01:31:28,400
Maybe you can talk him to death.

879
01:32:42,280 --> 01:32:45,120
COP 1: The bus, the tour bus, second level.

880
01:32:46,400 --> 01:32:48,240
COP 2: Negative on the target.

881
01:32:50,960 --> 01:32:53,000
COP 4: Position one?
COP 2: Negative.

882
01:32:53,120 --> 01:32:55,240
COP 4: Position two?
COP 3: Negative.

883
01:33:09,600 --> 01:33:12,080
COP 1: Position three, motorcycle.

884
01:33:13,080 --> 01:33:14,360
COP 3: Negative.

885
01:33:14,520 --> 01:33:15,520
COP 5: Negative.

886
01:33:38,800 --> 01:33:39,840
Jason?

887
01:33:39,920 --> 01:33:43,680
I told you to come alone.
I guess that was too complicated.

888
01:33:43,760 --> 01:33:45,520
BOURNE: So try this: I'm gone.

889
01:33:49,560 --> 01:33:50,520
Fuck.

890
01:33:57,280 --> 01:33:59,040
CONKLIN: Get Nicky on the phone.

891
01:34:14,040 --> 01:34:15,040
NICKY: Yeah?

892
01:34:15,120 --> 01:34:17,560
CONKLIN: How long to wipe down the room
and move it?

893
01:34:17,640 --> 01:34:19,520
NICKY: Get rid of everything?
CONKLIN: Yeah.

894
01:34:20,200 --> 01:34:22,840
NICKY: Two to three hours.
CONKLIN: All right, get started.

895
01:34:29,680 --> 01:34:30,920
Listen, no breaks.

896
01:34:31,000 --> 01:34:33,760
Two men outside, one in the lobby.
And keep your eyes open.

897
01:34:36,320 --> 01:34:38,480
COP 1: Keep the truck?
CONKLIN: Keep the truck.

898
01:34:38,680 --> 01:34:41,640
I'm gonna close this unit down.
We'll move the gear in the truck.

899
01:34:58,200 --> 01:35:00,840
NICKY:
They were covering Spain, Malta, Morocco.

900
01:35:00,920 --> 01:35:03,400
Yes, all local police radio traffic.

901
01:35:03,480 --> 01:35:06,880
No, for northern Europe
we need an authorised directive. Yeah.

902
01:35:07,960 --> 01:35:11,120
Okay, they're on it. We'll have
a satellite download in 30 minutes.

903
01:36:17,800 --> 01:36:19,640
CONKLIN: Where's your field box?

904
01:36:24,080 --> 01:36:26,760
- Where's your field box?
- It's right there.

905
01:36:27,600 --> 01:36:29,840
NICKY: The whole system's gone haywire.

906
01:36:30,240 --> 01:36:32,400
That's this window right here.

907
01:36:32,720 --> 01:36:34,440
Dining room window?

908
01:36:36,040 --> 01:36:37,520
I don't get it.

909
01:36:39,560 --> 01:36:41,560
Dead. The phones are dead.

910
01:36:43,560 --> 01:36:44,920
It's Bourne, isn't it?

911
01:36:45,920 --> 01:36:47,240
Just quiet.

912
01:37:33,040 --> 01:37:34,640
You move, you die.

913
01:37:34,880 --> 01:37:35,880
CONKLIN: Bourne.

914
01:37:36,240 --> 01:37:37,480
Gun down.

915
01:37:43,280 --> 01:37:44,240
In there.

916
01:37:45,960 --> 01:37:47,640
Okay, so what do you want...

917
01:37:47,760 --> 01:37:49,080
BOURNE: Treadstone.

918
01:37:49,600 --> 01:37:52,040
You better take a look around.
There's not much left.

919
01:37:52,120 --> 01:37:54,480
- Are you Treadstone?
- Am I Treadstone? Me?

920
01:37:54,560 --> 01:37:56,520
What the hell are you talking about?

921
01:37:56,600 --> 01:37:58,000
He's lost it.

922
01:37:58,200 --> 01:38:02,240
You better start filling in the blanks here!
'Cause I thought we were on the same side.

923
01:38:02,360 --> 01:38:03,520
Whose side is that?

924
01:38:03,640 --> 01:38:07,320
You don't know what you're doing, do you?
You don't have a goddamn clue!

925
01:38:07,640 --> 01:38:08,880
Who am I?

926
01:38:09,120 --> 01:38:11,000
You're U. S. Government property!

927
01:38:11,120 --> 01:38:14,160
You're a malfunctioning $30 million weapon!

928
01:38:14,640 --> 01:38:16,480
You're a total goddamn catastrophe!

929
01:38:16,600 --> 01:38:19,520
And, by God, if it kills me,
you'll tell me how this happened.

930
01:38:19,640 --> 01:38:22,480
- Why are you trying to kill me?
- What happened in Marseilles?

931
01:38:22,960 --> 01:38:25,160
You sent me to kill Wombosi.

932
01:38:25,240 --> 01:38:28,160
Kill Wombosi?
Yeah, we can do that any time we want.

933
01:38:28,240 --> 01:38:30,520
I can send Nicky to do that,
for Christ's sake.

934
01:38:31,040 --> 01:38:33,760
Mr. Wombosi was supposed to be dead
three weeks ago.

935
01:38:33,840 --> 01:38:37,360
He was supposed to have died in a way
that the only possible explanation was...

936
01:38:37,440 --> 01:38:40,360
...that he'd been murdered
by a member of his own entourage.

937
01:38:40,440 --> 01:38:42,160
I don't send you to kill.

938
01:38:42,280 --> 01:38:43,840
I send you to be invisible.

939
01:38:43,920 --> 01:38:46,080
I send you because you don't exist.

940
01:38:46,440 --> 01:38:48,480
I want to know what happened in Marseilles.

941
01:38:48,560 --> 01:38:51,240
I don't remember what happened
in Marseilles.

942
01:38:51,320 --> 01:38:53,880
Bullshit! This is unacceptable, soldier.

943
01:38:53,960 --> 01:38:55,560
You hear me? You failed!

944
01:38:55,640 --> 01:38:57,040
- Unacceptable?
- You failed!

945
01:38:57,160 --> 01:39:00,680
- You failed and you're gonna tell me why!
- I can't tell you! I don't remember!

946
01:39:00,760 --> 01:39:03,720
You brought Kane to life.
You put together a meeting with Wombosi.

947
01:39:03,920 --> 01:39:06,440
You found the security company.
You broke into the office!

948
01:39:06,520 --> 01:39:10,160
For Christ's sake, you picked the yacht
as the goddamn strike point!

949
01:39:17,720 --> 01:39:19,480
CONKLIN: You picked the boat.

950
01:39:19,560 --> 01:39:21,880
You picked the day. You tracked the crew.

951
01:39:21,960 --> 01:39:23,440
The food, the fuel!

952
01:39:23,520 --> 01:39:26,160
You told us where. You told us when.

953
01:39:26,720 --> 01:39:29,160
You hid out on that boat five days.

954
01:39:29,320 --> 01:39:31,800
You were in, Jason. You were in!

955
01:39:31,880 --> 01:39:33,320
It was over!

956
01:40:31,480 --> 01:40:33,200
CONKLIN: No, you do remember.

957
01:40:36,080 --> 01:40:37,400
Don't you?

958
01:40:43,520 --> 01:40:45,480
I don't want to do this anymore.

959
01:40:46,520 --> 01:40:48,960
I don't think that's a decision you can make.

960
01:40:53,640 --> 01:40:56,200
Jason Bourne is dead. Do you hear me?

961
01:40:56,600 --> 01:40:58,240
BOURNE: He drowned two weeks ago.

962
01:40:58,520 --> 01:41:00,760
You're gonna go tell them Bourne is dead.
Understand?

963
01:41:00,840 --> 01:41:02,280
CONKLIN: Where are you gonna go?

964
01:41:03,440 --> 01:41:07,160
I swear, if I even feel somebody behind me,
there is no measure to how fast...

965
01:41:07,240 --> 01:41:10,200
...and how hard I will bring this fight
to your doorstep.

966
01:41:10,320 --> 01:41:12,160
I'm on my own side now.

967
01:44:38,320 --> 01:44:39,280
It's done.

968
01:44:40,200 --> 01:44:41,600
Shut it down.

969
01:45:18,160 --> 01:45:20,920
ABBOTT: The Treadstone project
has already been terminated.

970
01:45:21,000 --> 01:45:24,080
It was designed primarily
as a sort of advanced game program.

971
01:45:24,160 --> 01:45:26,760
We'd hoped it might build
into a good training platform.

972
01:45:26,840 --> 01:45:30,280
But quite honestly,
for a strictly theoretical exercise...

